President Donald J. Trump met with President Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa of Portugal at the White House on June 27, 2018. The visit was part of the Month of Portugal celebration in the United States, which highlighted the cultural and economic connections between the two countries. The two leaders discussed increasing security and economic cooperation, such as diversifying European energy resources and working together to strengthen NATO. They also discussed Portugal's plans to meet the defense spending targets set by the Alliance.